sectionContent['introduction'] = "<h1>Introduction</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>Welcome to the <strong>School Management System</strong> documentation. This comprehensive guide will help you understand, implement, and extend the features of our modern educational management platform.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"info-box\">\r\n    <h4>About This System</h4>\r\n    <p>The School Management System is a full-stack web application built with Next.js, React, and TypeScript. It provides a complete solution for managing students, teachers, parents, classes, attendance, results, fees, and more.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h2>System Overview</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The School Management System is designed to streamline administrative tasks, enhance communication between stakeholders, and provide real-time insights into academic performance and school operations.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"assets/screenshots/login-page.png\" alt=\"User Login Interface\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 1: User Login Interface</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h2>Key Features</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"feature-grid\">\r\n    <div class=\"feature-card\">\r\n        <h4>ðŸ‘¥ Multi-Role System</h4>\r\n        <p>Support for Admin, Teacher, Student, and Parent roles with role-based access control and customized dashboards.</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class=\"feature-card\">\r\n        <h4>ðŸ“š Academic Management</h4>\r\n        <p>Complete management of classes, subjects, schedules, and academic sessions with flexible configuration options.</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class=\"feature-card\">\r\n        <h4>ðŸ“Š Attendance Tracking</h4>\r\n        <p>Real-time attendance marking, viewing, and reporting for students with detailed analytics and history.</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class=\"feature-card\">\r\n        <h4>ðŸ“ Results Management</h4>\r\n        <p>Comprehensive results entry, viewing, and management system with support for multiple assessment types.</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class=\"feature-card\">\r\n        <h4>ðŸ’° Fee Management</h4>\r\n        <p>Complete fee structure management, payment tracking, and financial reporting for students and parents.</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class=\"feature-card\">\r\n        <h4>ðŸ“– Bookshop Integration</h4>\r\n        <p>Integrated bookshop management system for tracking book inventory, sales, and assignments to students.</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h2>Technology Stack</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>Frontend</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><strong>Next.js 16.1.1</strong> - React framework with server-side rendering</li>\r\n    <li><strong>React 19.2.3</strong> - UI library</li>\r\n    <li><strong>TypeScript</strong> - Type-safe JavaScript</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Ant Design (antd)</strong> - UI component library</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Tailwind CSS</strong> - Utility-first CSS framework</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Axios</strong> - HTTP client for API requests</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Backend</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><strong>Laravel/PHP</strong> - Backend API (assumed based on API structure)</li>\r\n    <li><strong>MySQL/PostgreSQL</strong> - Database management system</li>\r\n    <li><strong>RESTful API</strong> - API architecture</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Project Structure</h2>\r\n\r\n<pre><code>school-frontend/\r\nâ”œâ”€â”€ app/\r\nâ”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ admin/          # Admin-specific pages\r\nâ”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ dashboard/      # Student dashboard\r\nâ”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ teachers/       # Teacher-specific pages\r\nâ”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ parent/         # Parent-specific pages\r\nâ”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ components/     # Reusable React components\r\nâ”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ lib/            # Utility functions and API client\r\nâ”‚   â””â”€â”€ login/          # Authentication pages\r\nâ”œâ”€â”€ docs/               # Documentation (this folder)\r\nâ”œâ”€â”€ public/             # Static assets\r\nâ””â”€â”€ package.json        # Dependencies and scripts\r\n</code></pre>\r\n\r\n<h2>Getting Started</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>Prerequisites</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Node.js 18+ and npm/yarn</li>\r\n    <li>Backend API server running (default: http://127.0.0.1:8000)</li>\r\n    <li>Modern web browser (Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Installation</h3>\r\n\r\n<pre><code># Clone the repository\r\ngit clone [repository-url]\r\n\r\n# Navigate to project directory\r\ncd school-frontend\r\n\r\n# Install dependencies\r\nnpm install\r\n\r\n# Set up environment variables\r\n# Create .env.local file with:\r\n# NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8000/api\r\n# NEXT_PUBLIC_BACKEND_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8000\r\n\r\n# Run development server\r\nnpm run dev\r\n\r\n# Build for production\r\nnpm run build\r\nnpm start\r\n</code></pre>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"important-box\">\r\n    <h4>Important!</h4>\r\n    <p>Make sure your backend API server is running before starting the frontend application. The frontend communicates with the backend through RESTful API endpoints.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h2>System Architecture</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The system follows a client-server architecture with clear separation of concerns:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><strong>Frontend:</strong> Next.js application handling UI/UX and user interactions</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Backend API:</strong> RESTful API providing data and business logic</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Database:</strong> Relational database storing all system data</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Authentication:</strong> Token-based authentication using JWT</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>User Roles</h2>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n    <thead>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <th>Role</th>\r\n            <th>Description</th>\r\n            <th>Key Permissions</th>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </thead>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><strong>Admin</strong></td>\r\n            <td>System administrator with full access</td>\r\n            <td>Manage users, classes, subjects, fees, results, and all system settings</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><strong>Teacher</strong></td>\r\n            <td>Educator managing classes and students</td>\r\n            <td>Mark attendance, enter results, view assigned classes and students</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><strong>Student</strong></td>\r\n            <td>Learner accessing academic information</td>\r\n            <td>View attendance, results, fees, class schedule, and personal information</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><strong>Parent</strong></td>\r\n            <td>Guardian monitoring child's progress</td>\r\n            <td>View child's attendance, results, fees, and academic information</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h2>Next Steps</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Now that you have an overview of the system, explore the following sections:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><a href=\"#\" onclick=\"event.preventDefault(); document.querySelector('[data-section=authentication]')?.click();\">Authentication & Authorization</a> - Learn about login, registration, and role-based access</li>\r\n    <li><a href=\"#\" onclick=\"event.preventDefault(); document.querySelector('[data-section=student]')?.click();\">Student Functionality</a> - Discover student features and capabilities</li>\r\n    <li><a href=\"#\" onclick=\"event.preventDefault(); document.querySelector('[data-section=teacher]')?.click();\">Teacher Functionality</a> - Explore teacher tools and features</li>\r\n    <li><a href=\"#\" onclick=\"event.preventDefault(); document.querySelector('[data-section=admin]')?.click();\">Admin Functionality</a> - Master administrative features</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"success-box\">\r\n    <h4>Ready to Get Started?</h4>\r\n    <p>Follow the documentation sections in order for the best learning experience. Each section builds upon the previous one, providing you with comprehensive knowledge of the system.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n";
sectionContent['authentication'] = "<h1>Authentication & Authorization</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>The School Management System implements a secure, token-based authentication system that supports multiple user roles and provides role-based access control (RBAC) throughout the application.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"assets/screenshots/login-page.png\" alt=\"User Login Interface\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 1: User Login Interface</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h2>Authentication Flow</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The authentication process follows these steps:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n    <li>User enters credentials (email and password) on the login page</li>\r\n    <li>Frontend sends credentials to the backend API</li>\r\n    <li>Backend validates credentials and returns a JWT token</li>\r\n    <li>Frontend stores the token in localStorage</li>\r\n    <li>All subsequent API requests include the token in headers</li>\r\n    <li>User is redirected to their role-specific dashboard</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h2>Login Process</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>Login Endpoint</h3>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n    <thead>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <th>Method</th>\r\n            <th>Endpoint</th>\r\n            <th>Description</th>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </thead>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><code>POST</code></td>\r\n            <td><code>/api/login</code></td>\r\n            <td>Authenticate user and receive JWT token</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3>Request Body</h3>\r\n\r\n<pre><code>{\r\n  \"email\": \"user@example.com\",\r\n  \"password\": \"password123\"\r\n}\r\n</code></pre>\r\n\r\n<h3>Response</h3>\r\n\r\n<pre><code>{\r\n  \"status\": \"success\",\r\n  \"token\": \"eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...\",\r\n  \"user\": {\r\n    \"uuid\": \"user-uuid-here\",\r\n    \"name\": \"John Doe\",\r\n    \"email\": \"user@example.com\",\r\n    \"role\": \"student\",\r\n    \"phone\": \"08012345678\"\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n</code></pre>\r\n\r\n<h3>Implementation Example</h3>\r\n\r\n<pre><code>import api from '@/app/lib/api';\r\n\r\nconst onLogin = async (email: string, password: string) => {\r\n  try {\r\n    const response = await api.post('/login', {\r\n      email,\r\n      password\r\n    });\r\n\r\n    if (response.data.token) {\r\n      // Store token and user data\r\n      localStorage.setItem('token', response.data.token);\r\n      localStorage.setItem('user', JSON.stringify(response.data.user));\r\n\r\n      // Redirect based on role\r\n      const role = response.data.user?.role;\r\n      if (role === 'admin') {\r\n        router.push('/admin/dashboard');\r\n      } else if (role === 'teacher') {\r\n        router.push('/teachers/attendance');\r\n      } else if (role === 'parent') {\r\n        router.push('/parent/children');\r\n      } else {\r\n        router.push('/dashboard/student');\r\n      }\r\n    }\r\n  } catch (error) {\r\n    console.error('Login failed:', error);\r\n  }\r\n};\r\n</code></pre>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"assets/screenshots/login-success.png\" alt=\"Login Success Redirect\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 2: Post-Login Dashboard Redirect</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h2>Token Management</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>Storing Tokens</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Tokens are stored in the browser's <code>localStorage</code> for persistence across sessions:</p>\r\n\r\n<pre><code>// Store token\r\nlocalStorage.setItem('token', token);\r\n\r\n// Retrieve token\r\nconst token = localStorage.getItem('token');\r\n\r\n// Remove token (logout)\r\nlocalStorage.removeItem('token');\r\nlocalStorage.removeItem('user');\r\n</code></pre>\r\n\r\n<h3>Including Tokens in Requests</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>All authenticated API requests must include the token in the Authorization header:</p>\r\n\r\n<pre><code>import axios from 'axios';\r\nimport { getAuthHeaders } from '@/app/lib/auth';\r\n\r\n// GET request with auth\r\nconst response = await axios.get(\r\n  'http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/students',\r\n  getAuthHeaders()\r\n);\r\n\r\n// POST request with auth\r\nconst response = await axios.post(\r\n  'http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/admin/students',\r\n  studentData,\r\n  getAuthHeaders()\r\n);\r\n</code></pre>\r\n\r\n<h3>Auth Headers Helper</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The <code>getAuthHeaders()</code> function automatically includes the token:</p>\r\n\r\n<pre><code>// app/lib/auth.ts\r\nexport function getAuthHeaders() {\r\n  const token = localStorage.getItem('token');\r\n  return {\r\n    headers: {\r\n      'Authorization': `Bearer ${token}`,\r\n      'Content-Type': 'application/json',\r\n      'Accept': 'application/json'\r\n    }\r\n  };\r\n}\r\n</code></pre>\r\n\r\n<h2>Role-Based Access Control</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The system supports four distinct user roles, each with specific permissions and access levels:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Role Definitions</h3>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n    <thead>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <th>Role</th>\r\n            <th>Dashboard Route</th>\r\n            <th>Key Features</th>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </thead>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><strong>Admin</strong></td>\r\n            <td><code>/admin/dashboard</code></td>\r\n            <td>Full system access, user management, settings</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><strong>Teacher</strong></td>\r\n            <td><code>/teachers/attendance</code></td>\r\n            <td>Attendance marking, results entry, class management</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><strong>Student</strong></td>\r\n            <td><code>/dashboard/student</code></td>\r\n            <td>View attendance, results, fees, schedule</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><strong>Parent</strong></td>\r\n            <td><code>/parent/children</code></td>\r\n            <td>View child's academic information and fees</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"assets/screenshots/role-dashboards.png\" alt=\"Role-Based Dashboards\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 3: Different Dashboards for Each Role</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h2>Protected Routes</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Routes are protected based on user roles. The system checks authentication status and redirects unauthenticated users to the login page.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Route Protection Implementation</h3>\r\n\r\n<pre><code>// Example: Admin route protection\r\n'use client';\r\n\r\nimport { useEffect } from 'react';\r\nimport { useRouter } from 'next/navigation';\r\n\r\nexport default function AdminPage() {\r\n  const router = useRouter();\r\n\r\n  useEffect(() => {\r\n    const userStr = localStorage.getItem('user');\r\n    if (!userStr) {\r\n      router.push('/login');\r\n      return;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    const user = JSON.parse(userStr);\r\n    if (user.role !== 'admin') {\r\n      router.push('/login');\r\n      return;\r\n    }\r\n  }, [router]);\r\n\r\n  // Page content...\r\n}\r\n</code></pre>\r\n\r\n<h2>Logout</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>Logout Endpoint</h3>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n    <thead>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <th>Method</th>\r\n            <th>Endpoint</th>\r\n            <th>Description</th>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </thead>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><code>POST</code></td>\r\n            <td><code>/api/logout</code></td>\r\n            <td>Invalidate token and log out user</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3>Logout Implementation</h3>\r\n\r\n<pre><code>const handleLogout = async () => {\r\n  try {\r\n    await api.post('/logout', {}, getAuthHeaders());\r\n  } catch (error) {\r\n    console.error('Logout error:', error);\r\n  } finally {\r\n    // Clear local storage\r\n    localStorage.removeItem('token');\r\n    localStorage.removeItem('user');\r\n    \r\n    // Redirect to login\r\n    router.push('/login');\r\n  }\r\n};\r\n</code></pre>\r\n\r\n<h2>Registration</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>New users can register through the registration endpoint. The registration process varies by role:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Registration Endpoint</h3>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n    <thead>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <th>Method</th>\r\n            <th>Endpoint</th>\r\n            <th>Description</th>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </thead>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><code>POST</code></td>\r\n            <td><code>/api/register</code></td>\r\n            <td>Register a new user account</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3>Request Body</h3>\r\n\r\n<pre><code>{\r\n  \"name\": \"John Doe\",\r\n  \"email\": \"john.doe@example.com\",\r\n  \"phone\": \"08012345678\",\r\n  \"password\": \"password123\",\r\n  \"password_confirmation\": \"password123\",\r\n  \"role\": \"student\",\r\n  \"parent_id\": null  // Required for student role\r\n}\r\n</code></pre>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"important-box\">\r\n    <h4>Important!</h4>\r\n    <p>Student registration requires a valid <code>parent_id</code>. Parents must be registered first before their children can be registered as students.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h2>Error Handling</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The authentication system includes comprehensive error handling:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><strong>Invalid Credentials:</strong> Returns 401 status with error message</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Token Expired:</strong> Automatically redirects to login page</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Unauthorized Access:</strong> Shows error message and redirects</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Network Errors:</strong> Displays user-friendly error messages</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Error Response Format</h3>\r\n\r\n<pre><code>{\r\n  \"status\": \"error\",\r\n  \"message\": \"Invalid email or password\",\r\n  \"errors\": {\r\n    \"email\": [\"The email field is required.\"],\r\n    \"password\": [\"The password field is required.\"]\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n</code></pre>\r\n\r\n<h2>Security Best Practices</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"info-box\">\r\n    <h4>Security Recommendations</h4>\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li>Always use HTTPS in production</li>\r\n        <li>Implement token refresh mechanism for long sessions</li>\r\n        <li>Validate and sanitize all user inputs</li>\r\n        <li>Implement rate limiting on login endpoints</li>\r\n        <li>Use secure password hashing (bcrypt, Argon2)</li>\r\n        <li>Implement CSRF protection</li>\r\n        <li>Set appropriate token expiration times</li>\r\n        <li>Log authentication attempts for security monitoring</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h2>API Interceptors</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The system uses Axios interceptors to automatically handle authentication:</p>\r\n\r\n<pre><code>// app/lib/api.ts\r\nimport axios from 'axios';\r\n\r\nconst api = axios.create({\r\n  baseURL: process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL || '/api',\r\n  withCredentials: true\r\n});\r\n\r\n// Request interceptor - Add token to requests\r\napi.interceptors.request.use(\r\n  (config) => {\r\n    const token = localStorage.getItem('token');\r\n    if (token) {\r\n      config.headers.Authorization = `Bearer ${token}`;\r\n    }\r\n    return config;\r\n  },\r\n  (error) => Promise.reject(error)\r\n);\r\n\r\n// Response interceptor - Handle token expiration\r\napi.interceptors.response.use(\r\n  (response) => response,\r\n  (error) => {\r\n    if (error.response?.status === 401) {\r\n      localStorage.removeItem('token');\r\n      localStorage.removeItem('user');\r\n      window.location.href = '/login';\r\n    }\r\n    return Promise.reject(error);\r\n  }\r\n);\r\n</code></pre>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"success-box\">\r\n    <h4>Next Steps</h4>\r\n    <p>Now that you understand authentication, explore the role-specific features in the Student, Teacher, Admin, and Parent sections.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n";
sectionContent['student'] = "<h1>Student Functionality</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>The Student module provides students with access to their academic information, attendance records, results, fees, class schedules, and personal profile management.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"../docimages/student%20login.png\" alt=\"User Login Interface\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 1: User Login Interface</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h2>Student Dashboard</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The student dashboard serves as the central hub where students can access all their academic information at a glance.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"../docimages/student dashboard pic.png\" alt=\"Student Dashboard\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 2: Student Dashboard Overview</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h3>Dashboard Features</h3>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"feature-grid\">\r\n    <div class=\"feature-card\">\r\n        <h4>ðŸ“Š Quick Statistics</h4>\r\n        <p>View total class members, upcoming classes, and recent results summary</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class=\"feature-card\">\r\n        <h4>ðŸ“… Tomorrow's Classes</h4>\r\n        <p>See upcoming classes for the next day with subject and time information</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class=\"feature-card\">\r\n        <h4>ðŸ“ˆ Academic Progress</h4>\r\n        <p>Track academic performance and progress over time</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h3>Dashboard API Endpoint</h3>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n    <thead>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <th>Method</th>\r\n            <th>Endpoint</th>\r\n            <th>Description</th>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </thead>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><code>GET</code></td>\r\n            <td><code>/api/notifications/next-daysubjects?uuid={student_uuid}</code></td>\r\n            <td>Get tomorrow's classes for a student</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h2>Student Pages & Features</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>1. Class Members</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Students can view all members of their class, including classmates and their basic information.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"../docimages/student class members.png\" alt=\"Student Class Members\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 3: Student Class Members View</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>Class Members Endpoints</h4>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n    <thead>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <th>Method</th>\r\n            <th>Endpoint</th>\r\n            <th>Description</th>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </thead>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><code>GET</code></td>\r\n            <td><code>/api/student/class-members?uuid={student_uuid}</code></td>\r\n            <td>Get all members of the student's class</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3>2. Subjects</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Students can view all subjects they are enrolled in, along with subject details and teacher information.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"../docimages/student  class subject.png\" alt=\"Student Subjects\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 4: Student Subjects View</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>Subjects Endpoints</h4>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n    <thead>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <th>Method</th>\r\n            <th>Endpoint</th>\r\n            <th>Description</th>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </thead>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><code>GET</code></td>\r\n            <td><code>/api/student/subjects?uuid={student_uuid}</code></td>\r\n            <td>Get all subjects for a student</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3>3. Timetable</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Students can view their complete class timetable showing all scheduled classes, subjects, teachers, and time slots for the current session.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"../docimages/student timetable.png\" alt=\"Student Timetable\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 5: Student Timetable View</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>Timetable Endpoints</h4>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n    <thead>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <th>Method</th>\r\n            <th>Endpoint</th>\r\n            <th>Description</th>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </thead>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><code>GET</code></td>\r\n            <td><code>/api/student/timetable?uuid={student_uuid}&session_id={session_id}&term_id={term_id}</code></td>\r\n            <td>Get student timetable for a specific session and term</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3>4. Results</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Students can access their academic results, including exam scores, test results, grades, teacher comments, and overall performance. Results can be viewed by session and term, and can be printed as a report.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"../docimages/student view result.png\" alt=\"Student Results\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 6: Student Results View</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>Results Features</h4>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"feature-grid\">\r\n    <div class=\"feature-card\">\r\n        <h4>ðŸ“Š Session & Term Selection</h4>\r\n        <p>Filter results by academic session and term</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class=\"feature-card\">\r\n        <h4>ðŸ“ Detailed Marks</h4>\r\n        <p>View CA1, CA2, Exam scores, totals, and grades</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class=\"feature-card\">\r\n        <h4>ðŸ’¬ Teacher Comments</h4>\r\n        <p>Read feedback and comments from teachers</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class=\"feature-card\">\r\n        <h4>ðŸ–¨ï¸ Print Report</h4>\r\n        <p>Generate and print official result reports</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>Results Endpoints</h4>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n    <thead>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <th>Method</th>\r\n            <th>Endpoint</th>\r\n            <th>Description</th>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </thead>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><code>GET</code></td>\r\n            <td><code>/api/student/results?uuid={student_uuid}&session_id={session_id}&term_id={term_id}</code></td>\r\n            <td>Get results for a specific session and term</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3>5. Previous Results</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Students can view their historical academic results from previous terms and sessions. This allows students to track their academic progress over time.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Previous Results Features</h4>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"feature-grid\">\r\n    <div class=\"feature-card\">\r\n        <h4>ðŸ“š Historical Data</h4>\r\n        <p>Access results from all previous terms and sessions</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class=\"feature-card\">\r\n        <h4>ðŸ“ˆ Progress Tracking</h4>\r\n        <p>Compare performance across different academic periods</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class=\"feature-card\">\r\n        <h4>ðŸ” Term Filtering</h4>\r\n        <p>Filter results by specific terms for easy navigation</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>Previous Results Endpoints</h4>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n    <thead>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <th>Method</th>\r\n            <th>Endpoint</th>\r\n            <th>Description</th>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </thead>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><code>GET</code></td>\r\n            <td><code>/api/student/previous-results?uuid={student_uuid}&term_id={term_id}</code></td>\r\n            <td>Get previous results for a specific term</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3>6. Session Details</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Students can view detailed information about their current academic session, including session name, start date, end date, and current status.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"../docimages/student view session.png\" alt=\"Student Session Details\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 7: Student Session Details View</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>Session Details Endpoints</h4>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n    <thead>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <th>Method</th>\r\n            <th>Endpoint</th>\r\n            <th>Description</th>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </thead>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><code>GET</code></td>\r\n            <td><code>/api/student/session-details?uuid={student_uuid}</code></td>\r\n            <td>Get current session details for a student</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3>7. Payment History</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Students can view their complete payment history, including all fee payments made, payment dates, amounts, payment methods, and transaction references.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"../docimages/student view payment history.png\" alt=\"Student Payment History\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 8: Student Payment History View</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>Payment History Features</h4>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"feature-grid\">\r\n    <div class=\"feature-card\">\r\n        <h4>ðŸ’° Payment Records</h4>\r\n        <p>View all past fee payments with detailed information</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class=\"feature-card\">\r\n        <h4>ðŸ“… Date Tracking</h4>\r\n        <p>See payment dates and transaction timestamps</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class=\"feature-card\">\r\n        <h4>ðŸ“„ Receipts</h4>\r\n        <p>Access payment receipts and transaction references</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>Payment History Endpoints</h4>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n    <thead>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <th>Method</th>\r\n            <th>Endpoint</th>\r\n            <th>Description</th>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </thead>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><code>GET</code></td>\r\n            <td><code>/api/student/payment-history?uuid={student_uuid}</code></td>\r\n            <td>Get payment history for a student</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3>8. Fee Obligations</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Students can view their current fee obligations, outstanding balances, due dates, and fee breakdowns. This helps students stay informed about their financial responsibilities.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"../docimages/student fee obligation.png\" alt=\"Student Fee Obligations\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 9: Student Fee Obligations View</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>Fee Obligations Features</h4>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"feature-grid\">\r\n    <div class=\"feature-card\">\r\n        <h4>ðŸ’µ Fee Breakdown</h4>\r\n        <p>View detailed breakdown of all fee components</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class=\"feature-card\">\r\n        <h4>â° Due Dates</h4>\r\n        <p>See payment due dates and deadlines</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class=\"feature-card\">\r\n        <h4>ðŸ“Š Outstanding Balance</h4>\r\n        <p>Track remaining balance and payment status</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>Fee Obligations Endpoints</h4>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n    <thead>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <th>Method</th>\r\n            <th>Endpoint</th>\r\n            <th>Description</th>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </thead>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><code>GET</code></td>\r\n            <td><code>/api/student/fee/obligations?uuid={student_uuid}</code></td>\r\n            <td>Get fee obligations for a student</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3>9. Profile Management</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Students can view and update their personal information, including name, email, phone number, and other profile details. This is the only section where students have write access.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"../docimages/student%20profile.png\" alt=\"Student Profile Management\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 10: Student Profile Management</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>Profile Features</h4>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"feature-grid\">\r\n    <div class=\"feature-card\">\r\n        <h4>ðŸ‘¤ Personal Information</h4>\r\n        <p>View and edit name, email, and contact details</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class=\"feature-card\">\r\n        <h4>ðŸ”’ Security</h4>\r\n        <p>Update password and security settings</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class=\"feature-card\">\r\n        <h4>ðŸ“ Account Details</h4>\r\n        <p>View account creation date and last update information</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>Profile Endpoints</h4>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n    <thead>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <th>Method</th>\r\n            <th>Endpoint</th>\r\n            <th>Description</th>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </thead>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><code>GET</code></td>\r\n            <td><code>/api/me?uuid={student_uuid}</code></td>\r\n            <td>Get student profile information</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><code>PUT</code></td>\r\n            <td><code>/api/me?uuid={student_uuid}</code></td>\r\n            <td>Update student profile</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h2>Student Routes</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>All student routes are prefixed with <code>/dashboard/student</code>:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><code>/dashboard/student</code> - Main dashboard</li>\r\n    <li><code>/dashboard/student/class-members</code> - View class members</li>\r\n    <li><code>/dashboard/student/subjects</code> - View enrolled subjects</li>\r\n    <li><code>/dashboard/student/timetable</code> - View class timetable</li>\r\n    <li><code>/dashboard/student/results</code> - View current results</li>\r\n    <li><code>/dashboard/student/prev-results</code> - View previous results</li>\r\n    <li><code>/dashboard/student/session-details</code> - View session information</li>\r\n    <li><code>/dashboard/student/payment-history</code> - View payment history</li>\r\n    <li><code>/dashboard/student/fee/obligations</code> - View fee obligations</li>\r\n    <li><code>/dashboard/student/profile</code> - Profile management</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Implementation Example</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>Fetching Student Data</h3>\r\n\r\n<pre><code>import axios from 'axios';\r\nimport { getAuthHeaders } from '@/app/lib/auth';\r\n\r\n// Get student UUID from localStorage\r\nconst getStudentUuid = () => {\r\n  const userStr = localStorage.getItem('user');\r\n  if (userStr) {\r\n    const user = JSON.parse(userStr);\r\n    return user?.uuid || null;\r\n  }\r\n  return null;\r\n};\r\n\r\n// Fetch tomorrow's classes\r\nconst fetchTomorrowClasses = async () => {\r\n  const studentUuid = getStudentUuid();\r\n  if (!studentUuid) return;\r\n\r\n  try {\r\n    const response = await axios.get(\r\n      \\`http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/notifications/next-daysubjects?uuid=\\${studentUuid}\\`,\r\n      getAuthHeaders()\r\n    );\r\n\r\n    if (response.data.status === 'success') {\r\n      const classes = response.data.notifications;\r\n      // Process and display classes\r\n    }\r\n  } catch (error) {\r\n    console.error('Error fetching classes:', error);\r\n  }\r\n};\r\n\r\n// Fetch results\r\nconst fetchResults = async (sessionId, termId) => {\r\n  const studentUuid = getStudentUuid();\r\n  if (!studentUuid) return;\r\n\r\n  try {\r\n    const response = await axios.get(\r\n      \\`http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/student/results?uuid=\\${studentUuid}&session_id=\\${sessionId}&term_id=\\${termId}\\`,\r\n      getAuthHeaders()\r\n    );\r\n\r\n    if (response.data.status === 'success') {\r\n      const results = response.data.results;\r\n      // Display results\r\n    }\r\n  } catch (error) {\r\n    console.error('Error fetching results:', error);\r\n  }\r\n};\r\n\r\n// Fetch payment history\r\nconst fetchPaymentHistory = async () => {\r\n  const studentUuid = getStudentUuid();\r\n  if (!studentUuid) return;\r\n\r\n  try {\r\n    const response = await axios.get(\r\n      \\`http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/student/payment-history?uuid=\\${studentUuid}\\`,\r\n      getAuthHeaders()\r\n    );\r\n\r\n    if (response.data.status === 'success') {\r\n      const payments = response.data.data;\r\n      // Display payment history\r\n    }\r\n  } catch (error) {\r\n    console.error('Error fetching payment history:', error);\r\n  }\r\n};\r\n</code></pre>\r\n\r\n<h2>Key Features Summary</h2>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n    <thead>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <th>Feature</th>\r\n            <th>Description</th>\r\n            <th>Access Level</th>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </thead>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>Dashboard</td>\r\n            <td>Overview of academic information and statistics</td>\r\n            <td>Read-only</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>Class Members</td>\r\n            <td>View all members of the student's class</td>\r\n            <td>Read-only</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>Subjects</td>\r\n            <td>View enrolled subjects and subject details</td>\r\n            <td>Read-only</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>Timetable</td>\r\n            <td>View class schedule and timetable</td>\r\n            <td>Read-only</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>Results</td>\r\n            <td>View current academic results and performance</td>\r\n            <td>Read-only</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>Previous Results</td>\r\n            <td>View historical academic results</td>\r\n            <td>Read-only</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>Session Details</td>\r\n            <td>View current academic session information</td>\r\n            <td>Read-only</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>Payment History</td>\r\n            <td>View fee payment history and receipts</td>\r\n            <td>Read-only</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>Fee Obligations</td>\r\n            <td>View current fee obligations and outstanding balances</td>\r\n            <td>Read-only</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>Profile</td>\r\n            <td>View and update personal information</td>\r\n            <td>Read/Write</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"important-box\">\r\n    <h4>Important Notes</h4>\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li>Students have read-only access to most academic information</li>\r\n        <li>Only profile information can be updated by students</li>\r\n        <li>All data is filtered by the student's UUID for security</li>\r\n        <li>Students can only view their own information</li>\r\n        <li>Results can be filtered by session and term for better organization</li>\r\n        <li>Payment history provides complete transaction records for reference</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"success-box\">\r\n    <h4>Next Steps</h4>\r\n    <p>Explore the Teacher and Admin sections to see how academic data is created and managed.</p>\r\n</div>";
sectionContent['teacher'] = "<h1>Teacher Functionality</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>The Teacher module empowers educators to manage their classes, mark attendance, enter results, and track student performance. Teachers have access to tools specifically designed for classroom management and academic assessment.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"../docimages/teacher login.png\" alt=\"User Login Interface\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 1: User Login Interface</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h2>Teacher Dashboard</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The teacher dashboard provides a comprehensive overview of teaching activities, including statistics on students, classes, subjects, attendance, and results. Teachers can quickly access key information and navigate to important features.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"../docimages/teacher dashboard.png\" alt=\"Teacher Dashboard\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 2: Teacher Dashboard Overview</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h3>Dashboard Statistics</h3>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"feature-grid\">\r\n    <div class=\"feature-card\">\r\n        <h4>ðŸ‘¥ Total Students</h4>\r\n        <p>Number of students across all assigned classes</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class=\"feature-card\">\r\n        <h4>ðŸ“š Total Classes</h4>\r\n        <p>Number of classes assigned to the teacher</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class=\"feature-card\">\r\n        <h4>ðŸ“– Total Subjects</h4>\r\n        <p>Number of subjects the teacher is teaching</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class=\"feature-card\">\r\n        <h4>âœ… Attendance Marked Today</h4>\r\n        <p>Number of attendance records marked for today</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class=\"feature-card\">\r\n        <h4>ðŸ“Š Results Entered</h4>\r\n        <p>Total number of results entered by the teacher</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class=\"feature-card\">\r\n        <h4>ðŸ“… Upcoming Classes</h4>\r\n        <p>Number of classes scheduled for today or tomorrow</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h3>Dashboard API Endpoint</h3>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n    <thead>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <th>Method</th>\r\n            <th>Endpoint</th>\r\n            <th>Description</th>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </thead>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><code>GET</code></td>\r\n            <td><code>/api/teachers/dashboard/stats</code></td>\r\n            <td>Get teacher dashboard statistics (to be implemented)</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h2>Core Features</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>1. Attendance Management</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Teachers can mark attendance for students in their assigned classes. This is one of the most frequently used features. The attendance management interface provides easy access to classes and students, allowing teachers to quickly mark daily attendance.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"assets/screenshots/teacher%20mark%20attendance.png\" alt=\"Teacher Attendance Marking\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 4: Marking Student Attendance</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>Update Attendance</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Teachers can update previously marked attendance records if corrections are needed.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"assets/screenshots/teacher%20update%20attendance.png\" alt=\"Update Attendance\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 4a: Update Attendance Records</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>Attendance Summary</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>View comprehensive attendance summaries with statistics and reports for students in assigned classes.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"assets/screenshots/teacher%20attendance%20summary.png\" alt=\"Attendance Summary\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 4b: Attendance Summary Report</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>Attendance Endpoints</h4>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n    <thead>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <th>Method</th>\r\n            <th>Endpoint</th>\r\n            <th>Description</th>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </thead>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><code>GET</code></td>\r\n            <td><code>/api/teachers/attendance/classes</code></td>\r\n            <td>Get classes assigned to teacher</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><code>GET</code></td>\r\n            <td><code>/api/teachers/attendance/students?class_id={id}</code></td>\r\n            <td>Get students in a class</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><code>POST</code></td>\r\n            <td><code>/api/teachers/attendance/mark</code></td>\r\n            <td>Mark attendance for students</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><code>GET</code></td>\r\n            <td><code>/api/teachers/attendance/summary</code></td>\r\n            <td>Get attendance summary</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h4>Marking Attendance Example</h4>\r\n\r\n<pre><code>const markAttendance = async (classId, date, attendanceData) => {\r\n  try {\r\n    const response = await axios.post(\r\n      'http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/teachers/attendance/mark',\r\n      {\r\n        class_id: classId,\r\n        date: date,\r\n        attendance: attendanceData  // Array of {student_uuid, status: 'present'|'absent'|'late'}\r\n      },\r\n      getAuthHeaders()\r\n    );\r\n\r\n    if (response.data.status === 'success') {\r\n      // Show success message\r\n      message.success('Attendance marked successfully');\r\n    }\r\n  } catch (error) {\r\n    console.error('Error marking attendance:', error);\r\n    message.error('Failed to mark attendance');\r\n  }\r\n};\r\n</code></pre>\r\n\r\n<h3>2. Results Management</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Teachers can enter, view, and update student results for various assessments including exams, tests, and assignments.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"assets/screenshots/teacher%20enter%20result.png\" alt=\"Entering Results\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 5: Entering Student Results</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>Results Management Endpoints</h4>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n    <thead>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <th>Method</th>\r\n            <th>Endpoint</th>\r\n            <th>Description</th>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </thead>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><code>GET</code></td>\r\n            <td><code>/api/teachers/results/classes</code></td>\r\n            <td>Get classes for results entry</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><code>GET</code></td>\r\n            <td><code>/api/teachers/results/subjects?class_id={id}</code></td>\r\n            <td>Get subjects for a class</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><code>POST</code></td>\r\n            <td><code>/api/teachers/results/enter</code></td>\r\n            <td>Enter results for students</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><code>GET</code></td>\r\n            <td><code>/api/teachers/results/view</code></td>\r\n            <td>View all results</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><code>PUT</code></td>\r\n            <td><code>/api/teachers/results/update/{result_id}</code></td>\r\n            <td>Update existing results</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><code>GET</code></td>\r\n            <td><code>/api/teachers/results/single/{result_id}</code></td>\r\n            <td>View single result details</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h4>Entering Results Example</h4>\r\n\r\n<pre><code>const enterResults = async (classId, subjectId, examType, results) => {\r\n  try {\r\n    const response = await axios.post(\r\n      'http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/teachers/results/enter',\r\n      {\r\n        class_id: classId,\r\n        subject_id: subjectId,\r\n        exam_type: examType,  // 'exam', 'test', 'assignment', etc.\r\n        session_id: currentSessionId,\r\n        results: results  // Array of {student_uuid, score, grade}\r\n      },\r\n      getAuthHeaders()\r\n    );\r\n\r\n    if (response.data.status === 'success') {\r\n      message.success('Results entered successfully');\r\n    }\r\n  } catch (error) {\r\n    console.error('Error entering results:', error);\r\n    message.error('Failed to enter results');\r\n  }\r\n};\r\n</code></pre>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"assets/screenshots/teacher%20view%20all%20results.png\" alt=\"Viewing Results\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 6: Viewing All Results</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>View Single Result</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Teachers can view detailed information for a single student's result, including all assessment components and teacher comments.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"assets/screenshots/teacher%20view%20single%20result.png\" alt=\"View Single Result\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 6a: View Single Student Result</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>Update Results</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Teachers can update existing result entries to correct scores or modify comments.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"assets/screenshots/teacher%20update%20result.png\" alt=\"Update Results\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 6b: Update Student Results</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h3>3. Class & Subject Management</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Teachers can view and manage their assigned classes and subjects, including viewing student lists and class schedules.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>View Students in Classes Taught</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Teachers can view all students in classes where they teach assigned subjects.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"assets/screenshots/teacher%20view%20students%20in%20class%20taught.png\" alt=\"View Students in Class Taught\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 7a: View Students in Classes Taught</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>View Students in Form Class</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Form teachers can view all students in their assigned form class.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"assets/screenshots/teacher%20view%20students%20in%20class%20he%20is%20form%20Teacher.png\" alt=\"View Form Class Students\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 7b: View Form Class Students</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>View Assigned Subjects</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Teachers can view a list of all subjects they are assigned to teach, organized by session.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"assets/screenshots/teacher%20view%20assigned%20subjects.png\" alt=\"View Assigned Subjects\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 7c: View Assigned Subjects</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>Class Management Endpoints</h4>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n    <thead>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <th>Method</th>\r\n            <th>Endpoint</th>\r\n            <th>Description</th>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </thead>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><code>GET</code></td>\r\n            <td><code>/api/teachers/classes</code></td>\r\n            <td>Get all classes assigned to teacher</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><code>GET</code></td>\r\n            <td><code>/api/teachers/subjects</code></td>\r\n            <td>Get all subjects assigned to teacher</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><code>GET</code></td>\r\n            <td><code>/api/teachers/class-subjects?class_id={id}</code></td>\r\n            <td>Get subjects for a specific class</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3>4. Attendance Summary</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Teachers can view comprehensive attendance summaries and statistics for their classes.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"assets/screenshots/teacher%20attendance%20summary.png\" alt=\"Attendance Summary\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 8: Attendance Summary and Statistics</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h2>Teacher Routes</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>All teacher routes are prefixed with <code>/teachers</code>:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><code>/teachers/dashboard</code> - Main dashboard with statistics</li>\r\n    <li><code>/teachers/attendance</code> - Mark and view attendance</li>\r\n    <li><code>/teachers/attendance/summary</code> - Attendance summary</li>\r\n    <li><code>/teachers/results/enter</code> - Enter student results</li>\r\n    <li><code>/teachers/results/view</code> - View all results</li>\r\n    <li><code>/teachers/results/update</code> - Update results</li>\r\n    <li><code>/teachers/results/single</code> - View single result</li>\r\n    <li><code>/teachers/class-subject-management</code> - Manage classes and subjects</li>\r\n    <li><code>/teachers/classes</code> - View assigned classes</li>\r\n    <li><code>/teachers/subjects</code> - View assigned subjects</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Implementation Example</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>Teacher Attendance Page</h3>\r\n\r\n<pre><code>// app/teachers/attendance/page.tsx\r\n'use client';\r\n\r\nimport { useState, useEffect } from 'react';\r\nimport { Card, Select, Table, Button, Space, message } from 'antd';\r\nimport axios from 'axios';\r\nimport { getAuthHeaders } from '@/app/lib/auth';\r\n\r\nexport default function TeacherAttendancePage() {\r\n  const [classes, setClasses] = useState([]);\r\n  const [selectedClass, setSelectedClass] = useState(null);\r\n  const [students, setStudents] = useState([]);\r\n  const [attendance, setAttendance] = useState({});\r\n  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(false);\r\n\r\n  useEffect(() => {\r\n    fetchClasses();\r\n  }, []);\r\n\r\n  const fetchClasses = async () => {\r\n    try {\r\n      const response = await axios.get(\r\n        'http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/teachers/attendance/classes',\r\n        getAuthHeaders()\r\n      );\r\n\r\n      if (response.data.status === 'success') {\r\n        setClasses(response.data.data);\r\n      }\r\n    } catch (error) {\r\n      console.error('Error fetching classes:', error);\r\n    }\r\n  };\r\n\r\n  const handleClassSelect = async (classId) => {\r\n    setSelectedClass(classId);\r\n    setLoading(true);\r\n\r\n    try {\r\n      const response = await axios.get(\r\n        `http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/teachers/attendance/students?class_id=${classId}`,\r\n        getAuthHeaders()\r\n      );\r\n\r\n      if (response.data.status === 'success') {\r\n        setStudents(response.data.data);\r\n      }\r\n    } catch (error) {\r\n      console.error('Error fetching students:', error);\r\n    } finally {\r\n      setLoading(false);\r\n    }\r\n  };\r\n\r\n  const handleAttendanceChange = (studentUuid, status) => {\r\n    setAttendance({\r\n      ...attendance,\r\n      [studentUuid]: status\r\n    });\r\n  };\r\n\r\n  const submitAttendance = async () => {\r\n    if (!selectedClass) return;\r\n\r\n    const attendanceData = Object.keys(attendance).map(studentUuid => ({\r\n      student_uuid: studentUuid,\r\n      status: attendance[studentUuid]\r\n    }));\r\n\r\n    try {\r\n      const response = await axios.post(\r\n        'http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/teachers/attendance/mark',\r\n        {\r\n          class_id: selectedClass,\r\n          date: new Date().toISOString().split('T')[0],\r\n          attendance: attendanceData\r\n        },\r\n        getAuthHeaders()\r\n      );\r\n\r\n      if (response.data.status === 'success') {\r\n        message.success('Attendance marked successfully');\r\n        setAttendance({});\r\n      }\r\n    } catch (error) {\r\n      console.error('Error marking attendance:', error);\r\n      message.error('Failed to mark attendance');\r\n    }\r\n  };\r\n\r\n  return (\r\n    <div className=\"teacher-attendance-page\">\r\n      <Card title=\"Mark Attendance\">\r\n        <Space direction=\"vertical\" style={{ width: '100%' }}>\r\n          <Select\r\n            placeholder=\"Select Class\"\r\n            style={{ width: '100%' }}\r\n            onChange={handleClassSelect}\r\n            loading={loading}\r\n          >\r\n            {classes.map(cls => (\r\n              <Select.Option key={cls.id} value={cls.id}>\r\n                {cls.class_name}\r\n              </Select.Option>\r\n            ))}\r\n          </Select>\r\n\r\n          {students.length > 0 && (\r\n            <>\r\n              <Table\r\n                dataSource={students}\r\n                columns={[\r\n                  {\r\n                    title: 'Student Name',\r\n                    dataIndex: 'name',\r\n                    key: 'name'\r\n                  },\r\n                  {\r\n                    title: 'Attendance',\r\n                    key: 'attendance',\r\n                    render: (_, record) => (\r\n                      <Select\r\n                        defaultValue=\"present\"\r\n                        onChange={(value) => handleAttendanceChange(record.uuid, value)}\r\n                      >\r\n                        <Select.Option value=\"present\">Present</Select.Option>\r\n                        <Select.Option value=\"absent\">Absent</Select.Option>\r\n                        <Select.Option value=\"late\">Late</Select.Option>\r\n                      </Select>\r\n                    )\r\n                  }\r\n                ]}\r\n              />\r\n\r\n              <Button type=\"primary\" onClick={submitAttendance}>\r\n                Submit Attendance\r\n              </Button>\r\n            </>\r\n          )}\r\n        </Space>\r\n      </Card>\r\n    </div>\r\n  );\r\n}\r\n</code></pre>\r\n\r\n<h2>Key Features Summary</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"../docimages/teacher dashboard.png\" alt=\"Key Features Summary\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 3: Key Features Summary</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n    <thead>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <th>Feature</th>\r\n            <th>Description</th>\r\n            <th>Access Level</th>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </thead>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>Attendance Marking</td>\r\n            <td>Mark daily attendance for students in assigned classes</td>\r\n            <td>Read/Write</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>Attendance Summary</td>\r\n            <td>View attendance statistics and summaries</td>\r\n            <td>Read-only</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>Results Entry</td>\r\n            <td>Enter exam, test, and assignment scores</td>\r\n            <td>Read/Write</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>Results Viewing</td>\r\n            <td>View all entered results with filtering options</td>\r\n            <td>Read-only</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>Results Update</td>\r\n            <td>Update previously entered results</td>\r\n            <td>Read/Write</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>Class Management</td>\r\n            <td>View assigned classes and student lists</td>\r\n            <td>Read-only</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>Subject Management</td>\r\n            <td>View assigned subjects and class-subject relationships</td>\r\n            <td>Read-only</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"important-box\">\r\n    <h4>Important Notes</h4>\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li>Teachers can only mark attendance and enter results for their assigned classes</li>\r\n        <li>Class and subject assignments are managed by administrators</li>\r\n        <li>Results can be updated before final submission</li>\r\n        <li>All actions are logged for audit purposes</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"success-box\">\r\n    <h4>Next Steps</h4>\r\n    <p>Learn about Admin functionality to understand how classes, subjects, and teacher assignments are managed.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n";
sectionContent['admin'] = "<h1>Admin Functionality</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>The Admin module provides comprehensive system administration capabilities, including user management, class and subject configuration, fee management, results oversight, bookshop management, announcements, and system-wide settings. Administrators have full control over all aspects of the school management system.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"../docimages/admin login.png\" alt=\"Admin Login Interface\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 1: Admin Login Interface</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h2>Admin Dashboard</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The admin dashboard provides a comprehensive overview of the entire school management system with key statistics and quick access to all administrative functions. It displays real-time data on students, teachers, fees, results, and other critical metrics.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"../docimages/admin dashboard.png\" alt=\"Admin Dashboard\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 2: Admin Dashboard Overview</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h2>Core Features</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>1. Student Management</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Administrators can manage all student records, including adding new students, viewing student lists, filtering students by various criteria, and promoting students to new classes.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Add Student</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Administrators can add new students to the system by entering their personal information, contact details, and class assignment. The system validates all required fields and ensures data integrity.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"../docimages/admin addstudent.png\" alt=\"Add Student\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 3: Add New Student</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>View All Students</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>View a comprehensive list of all students in the system with their details, including name, class, contact information, and enrollment status.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"../docimages/admin view all students.png\" alt=\"View All Students\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 4: View All Students</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>View Filtered Students</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Filter and view students based on various criteria such as class, session, term, or other attributes to quickly find specific student records.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"../docimages/admin view all filtered students.png\" alt=\"View Filtered Students\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 5: View Filtered Students</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>Promote Students</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Promote students to new classes or sessions. This feature allows bulk promotion of students and maintains academic progression records.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"../docimages/admin promote student.png\" alt=\"Promote Students\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 6: Promote Students to New Class</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h3>2. Teacher Management</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Administrators can manage teacher accounts, assign classes and subjects, and configure teacher permissions within the system.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Add Teacher</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Add new teachers to the system by entering their personal information, contact details, and initial assignments.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"../docimages/admin add teacher.png\" alt=\"Add Teacher\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 7: Add New Teacher</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>View All Teachers</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>View a comprehensive list of all teachers in the system with their details, assignments, and status.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"../docimages/admin view all teachers.png\" alt=\"View All Teachers\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 8: View All Teachers</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>Edit Teacher</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Update teacher information, modify assignments, and manage teacher account details.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"../docimages/admin edit teacher.png\" alt=\"Edit Teacher\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 9: Edit Teacher Information</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>Assign Subjects to Teachers</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Assign specific subjects to teachers for different classes and sessions. This determines which subjects each teacher can teach and manage.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"../docimages/admin assign subjects.png\" alt=\"Assign Subjects\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 10: Assign Subjects to Teachers</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>Assign Class to Teacher</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Assign form teacher responsibilities to teachers, designating them as the primary teacher for a specific class.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"../docimages/admin assign class to teacher.png\" alt=\"Assign Class to Teacher\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 11: Assign Class to Teacher</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>Add Subject to Class</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Configure which subjects are taught in each class, establishing the curriculum structure for different class levels.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"../docimages/admin add subject to class.png\" alt=\"Add Subject to Class\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 12: Add Subject to Class</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h3>3. Fee Management</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Comprehensive fee management system allowing administrators to create fees, track payments, view payment history, and manage fee obligations for students.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Add Fee</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Create new fee entries for students, specifying fee type, amount, due date, and associated class or session.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"../docimages/admin Add fee.png\" alt=\"Add Fee\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 13: Add New Fee</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>View Unpaid Fees</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>View all outstanding fees that have not been paid, allowing administrators to track payment status and follow up on overdue payments.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"../docimages/admin view unpaid fees.png\" alt=\"View Unpaid Fees\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 14: View Unpaid Fees</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>View Part Paid Fees</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>View fees that have been partially paid, showing the remaining balance and payment progress for each fee entry.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"../docimages/admin part paid .png\" alt=\"View Part Paid Fees\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 15: View Partially Paid Fees</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>View Completed Payments</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>View all fees that have been fully paid, providing a record of completed transactions.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"../docimages/admin view completed payments.png\" alt=\"View Completed Payments\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 16: View Completed Payments</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>Pay Fee</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Process fee payments for students, recording payment amounts, methods, and dates. Supports partial and full payments.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"../docimages/admin pay fee.png\" alt=\"Pay Fee\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 17: Process Fee Payment</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>View Student Payment History</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>View complete payment history for individual students, showing all transactions, payment dates, and amounts.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"../docimages/admin view student payment history.png\" alt=\"View Payment History\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 18: View Student Payment History</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>View Fee Obligation for Student</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>View all fee obligations for a specific student, including due dates, amounts, and payment status.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"../docimages/admin view fee obligation for student .png\" alt=\"View Fee Obligations\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 19: View Fee Obligations for Student</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h3>4. Results Management</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Administrators can enter, view, and update student results across all classes and subjects, providing oversight of academic performance.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Enter Result</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Enter student results including CA1, CA2, and exam scores. The system automatically calculates totals and assigns grades.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"../docimages/admin enter result.png\" alt=\"Enter Result\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 20: Enter Student Result</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>View All Results</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>View all student results across the system, with filtering options by session, term, class, and subject.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"../docimages/admin view all results.png\" alt=\"View All Results\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 21: View All Results</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>Update Result</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Update existing result entries to correct scores, modify grades, or adjust assessment components.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"../docimages/admin update result.png\" alt=\"Update Result\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 22: Update Student Result</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h3>5. Bookshop Management</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Complete bookshop management system for managing textbooks, assignments, and book sales across classes and terms.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Add Book</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Add new books to the bookshop inventory, specifying book details, price, class level, and term.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"../docimages/admin add book.png\" alt=\"Add Book\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 23: Add New Book</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>View All Books</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>View all books in the bookshop inventory, with details on availability, pricing, and class assignments.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"../docimages/admin view all books.png\" alt=\"View All Books\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 24: View All Books</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>Edit Book</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Update book information including title, author, price, and availability status.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"../docimages/admin edit book.png\" alt=\"Edit Book\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 25: Edit Book Information</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>Assign Book to Class</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Assign specific books to classes, determining which books are required for each class level and term.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"../docimages/admin assign book to class.png\" alt=\"Assign Book to Class\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 26: Assign Book to Class</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>View Book Requirements</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>View book requirements for different classes, showing which books are needed for each class level.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"../docimages/admin view book requirment.png\" alt=\"View Book Requirements\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 27: View Book Requirements</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>View Book Status</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>View the status of books including availability, stock levels, and assignment status across classes.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"../docimages/admin bookstatus.png\" alt=\"View Book Status\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 28: View Book Status</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>View All Books Sold</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>View sales records for all books, tracking purchases, revenue, and sales statistics.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"../docimages/admin view all books sold.png\" alt=\"View All Books Sold\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 29: View All Books Sold</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h3>6. Announcements Management</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Create and manage school-wide announcements to communicate important information to students, teachers, and parents.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Add Announcement</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Create new announcements with titles, content, target audience, and publication dates.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"../docimages/admin add announcment .png\" alt=\"Add Announcement\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 30: Add New Announcement</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>View Announcements</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>View all announcements in the system, including active, archived, and scheduled announcements.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"../docimages/admin view announcement.png\" alt=\"View Announcements\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 31: View All Announcements</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h3>7. Profile Management</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Administrators can view and update their own profile information, including personal details and account settings.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>View Profile</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>View administrator profile information including name, email, phone number, role, and account creation date.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"../docimages/admin view profile.png\" alt=\"View Profile\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 32: View Admin Profile</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h2>API Endpoints</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>Student Management Endpoints</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><strong>POST /api/admin/students</strong> - Add new student</li>\r\n    <li><strong>GET /api/admin/viewstudents</strong> - View all students (with optional filters)</li>\r\n    <li><strong>POST /api/admin/students/promote</strong> - Promote students to new class</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Teacher Management Endpoints</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><strong>POST /api/admin/teachers</strong> - Add new teacher</li>\r\n    <li><strong>GET /api/admin/teachers</strong> - View all teachers</li>\r\n    <li><strong>PUT /api/admin/teachers/{uuid}</strong> - Update teacher information</li>\r\n    <li><strong>POST /api/admin/teachers/assign-subject</strong> - Assign subject to teacher</li>\r\n    <li><strong>POST /api/admin/teachers/assign-class</strong> - Assign class to teacher</li>\r\n    <li><strong>POST /api/admin/classes/{class_id}/subjects</strong> - Add subject to class</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Fee Management Endpoints</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><strong>POST /api/admin/fees</strong> - Add new fee</li>\r\n    <li><strong>GET /api/admin/fees/unpaid</strong> - View unpaid fees</li>\r\n    <li><strong>GET /api/admin/fees/part-paid</strong> - View partially paid fees</li>\r\n    <li><strong>GET /api/admin/fees/paid</strong> - View completed payments</li>\r\n    <li><strong>POST /api/admin/fees/pay</strong> - Process fee payment</li>\r\n    <li><strong>GET /api/admin/fees/payment-history</strong> - View payment history</li>\r\n    <li><strong>GET /api/admin/fees/obligations</strong> - View fee obligations</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Results Management Endpoints</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><strong>POST /api/results/enter</strong> - Enter student result</li>\r\n    <li><strong>POST /api/results/view</strong> - View all results</li>\r\n    <li><strong>PUT /api/results/update/{id}</strong> - Update result</li>\r\n    <li><strong>GET /api/results/single/{id}</strong> - View single result</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Bookshop Management Endpoints</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><strong>POST /api/bookshop/books</strong> - Add new book</li>\r\n    <li><strong>GET /api/bookshop/books</strong> - View all books</li>\r\n    <li><strong>PUT /api/bookshop/books/{id}</strong> - Update book</li>\r\n    <li><strong>POST /api/bookshop/books/assign</strong> - Assign book to class</li>\r\n    <li><strong>GET /api/bookshop/books/requirements</strong> - View book requirements</li>\r\n    <li><strong>GET /api/bookshop/books/status</strong> - View book status</li>\r\n    <li><strong>GET /api/bookshop/sales</strong> - View all books sold</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Announcements Endpoints</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><strong>POST /api/admin/announcements</strong> - Add new announcement</li>\r\n    <li><strong>GET /api/admin/announcements</strong> - View all announcements</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Key Features</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"feature-grid\">\r\n    <div class=\"feature-card\">\r\n        <h4>👥 Student Management</h4>\r\n        <p>Complete student lifecycle management from enrollment to graduation with promotion capabilities</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class=\"feature-card\">\r\n        <h4>👨‍🏫 Teacher Management</h4>\r\n        <p>Manage teacher accounts, assignments, and class-subject configurations</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class=\"feature-card\">\r\n        <h4>💰 Fee Management</h4>\r\n        <p>Comprehensive fee tracking, payment processing, and financial reporting</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class=\"feature-card\">\r\n        <h4>📊 Results Oversight</h4>\r\n        <p>Enter, view, and update student results across all classes and subjects</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class=\"feature-card\">\r\n        <h4>📚 Bookshop Management</h4>\r\n        <p>Complete book inventory, assignment, and sales management system</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class=\"feature-card\">\r\n        <h4>📢 Announcements</h4>\r\n        <p>Create and manage school-wide announcements for all stakeholders</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class=\"feature-card\">\r\n        <h4>🔍 Advanced Filtering</h4>\r\n        <p>Filter and search across all modules by session, term, class, and more</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class=\"feature-card\">\r\n        <h4>📈 Dashboard Analytics</h4>\r\n        <p>Real-time statistics and insights on all system activities</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h2>Best Practices</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Regularly review and update student and teacher records to maintain data accuracy</li>\r\n    <li>Process fee payments promptly and keep accurate financial records</li>\r\n    <li>Use filtering and search features effectively to quickly locate specific records</li>\r\n    <li>Verify book assignments match curriculum requirements before publishing</li>\r\n    <li>Keep announcements clear, concise, and targeted to appropriate audiences</li>\r\n    <li>Review dashboard statistics regularly to monitor system health and usage</li>\r\n    <li>Maintain proper access controls and user permissions for security</li>\r\n    <li>Back up important data regularly and maintain audit trails for critical operations</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n";
sectionContent['parent'] = "<h1>Parent Functionality</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>The Parent module enables guardians to monitor their children's academic progress, view attendance records, check fee payments, and stay informed about their children's education.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"assets/screenshots/login-page.png\" alt=\"User Login Interface\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 1: User Login Interface</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h2>Parent Dashboard</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Upon login, parents are directed to a dashboard showing their children's information and quick access to academic data.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Core Features</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>1. Children Management</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Parents can view a list of all their registered children and access detailed information for each child.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"assets/screenshots/parent-children.png\" alt=\"Children List\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 2: Viewing Registered Children</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>Children Endpoints</h4>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n    <thead>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <th>Method</th>\r\n            <th>Endpoint</th>\r\n            <th>Description</th>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </thead>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><code>GET</code></td>\r\n            <td><code>/api/parent/children</code></td>\r\n            <td>Get all children for the parent</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><code>GET</code></td>\r\n            <td><code>/api/parent/children/{uuid}</code></td>\r\n            <td>Get detailed information for a specific child</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3>2. Child Details View</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Parents can view comprehensive information about each child, including personal details, class information, and academic summary.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"assets/screenshots/parent-child-details.png\" alt=\"Child Details\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 3: Detailed Child Information</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>Child Details Endpoints</h4>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n    <thead>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <th>Method</th>\r\n            <th>Endpoint</th>\r\n            <th>Description</th>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </thead>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><code>GET</code></td>\r\n            <td><code>/api/parent/children/{uuid}/details</code></td>\r\n            <td>Get complete child profile and academic information</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3>3. Attendance Monitoring</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Parents can view their children's attendance records, including present, absent, and late marks with detailed statistics.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"assets/screenshots/parent-attendance.png\" alt=\"Child Attendance\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 4: Viewing Child's Attendance Records</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>Attendance Endpoints</h4>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n    <thead>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <th>Method</th>\r\n            <th>Endpoint</th>\r\n            <th>Description</th>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </thead>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><code>GET</code></td>\r\n            <td><code>/api/parent/children/{uuid}/attendance</code></td>\r\n            <td>Get attendance records for a child</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><code>GET</code></td>\r\n            <td><code>/api/parent/children/{uuid}/attendance/summary</code></td>\r\n            <td>Get attendance summary statistics</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3>4. Academic Results</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Parents can view their children's academic results, including exam scores, test results, and overall performance across all subjects.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"assets/screenshots/parent-results.png\" alt=\"Child Results\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 5: Viewing Child's Academic Results</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>Academic Endpoints</h4>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n    <thead>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <th>Method</th>\r\n            <th>Endpoint</th>\r\n            <th>Description</th>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </thead>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><code>GET</code></td>\r\n            <td><code>/api/parent/children/{uuid}/academic</code></td>\r\n            <td>Get academic information for a child</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><code>GET</code></td>\r\n            <td><code>/api/parent/children/{uuid}/results</code></td>\r\n            <td>Get all results for a child</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><code>GET</code></td>\r\n            <td><code>/api/parent/children/{uuid}/results/{result_id}</code></td>\r\n            <td>Get specific result details</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3>5. Fee Management</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Parents can view fee obligations, payment history, and outstanding balances for their children.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"assets/screenshots/parent-fees.png\" alt=\"Child Fees\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 6: Viewing Child's Fee Information</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>Fee Endpoints</h4>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n    <thead>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <th>Method</th>\r\n            <th>Endpoint</th>\r\n            <th>Description</th>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </thead>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><code>GET</code></td>\r\n            <td><code>/api/parent/children/{uuid}/fees</code></td>\r\n            <td>Get fee information for a child</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><code>GET</code></td>\r\n            <td><code>/api/parent/children/{uuid}/fees/history</code></td>\r\n            <td>Get payment history</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><code>GET</code></td>\r\n            <td><code>/api/parent/children/{uuid}/fees/outstanding</code></td>\r\n            <td>Get outstanding fee balances</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3>6. Profile Management</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Parents can view and update their personal profile information.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"assets/screenshots/parent-profile.png\" alt=\"Parent Profile\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 7: Parent Profile Management</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>Profile Endpoints</h4>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n    <thead>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <th>Method</th>\r\n            <th>Endpoint</th>\r\n            <th>Description</th>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </thead>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><code>GET</code></td>\r\n            <td><code>/api/parent/profile</code></td>\r\n            <td>Get parent profile information</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><code>PUT</code></td>\r\n            <td><code>/api/parent/profile</code></td>\r\n            <td>Update parent profile</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h2>Parent Routes</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>All parent routes are prefixed with <code>/parent</code>:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><code>/parent/children</code> - List of registered children</li>\r\n    <li><code>/parent/children/{uuid}</code> - Detailed child information</li>\r\n    <li><code>/parent/attendance</code> - View children's attendance</li>\r\n    <li><code>/parent/academic</code> - View children's academic information</li>\r\n    <li><code>/parent/fees</code> - View fee information</li>\r\n    <li><code>/parent/profile</code> - Profile management</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Implementation Example</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>Parent Children Page</h3>\r\n\r\n<pre><code>// app/parent/children/page.tsx\r\n'use client';\r\n\r\nimport { useState, useEffect } from 'react';\r\nimport { Card, List, Avatar, Button, Spin } from 'antd';\r\nimport { UserOutlined } from '@ant-design/icons';\r\nimport { useRouter } from 'next/navigation';\r\nimport axios from 'axios';\r\nimport { getAuthHeaders } from '@/app/lib/auth';\r\n\r\ninterface Child {\r\n  uuid: string;\r\n  name: string;\r\n  email: string;\r\n  class_name: string;\r\n  phone?: string;\r\n}\r\n\r\nexport default function ParentChildrenPage() {\r\n  const [children, setChildren] = useState<Child[]>([]);\r\n  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true);\r\n  const router = useRouter();\r\n\r\n  useEffect(() => {\r\n    fetchChildren();\r\n  }, []);\r\n\r\n  const fetchChildren = async () => {\r\n    try {\r\n      const response = await axios.get(\r\n        'http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/parent/children',\r\n        getAuthHeaders()\r\n      );\r\n\r\n      if (response.data.status === 'success') {\r\n        setChildren(response.data.data);\r\n      }\r\n    } catch (error) {\r\n      console.error('Error fetching children:', error);\r\n    } finally {\r\n      setLoading(false);\r\n    }\r\n  };\r\n\r\n  const viewChildDetails = (childUuid: string) => {\r\n    router.push(`/parent/children/${childUuid}`);\r\n  };\r\n\r\n  if (loading) {\r\n    return <Spin size=\"large\" />;\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  return (\r\n    <div className=\"parent-children-page\">\r\n      <Card title=\"My Children\">\r\n        <List\r\n          dataSource={children}\r\n          renderItem={(child) => (\r\n            <List.Item\r\n              actions={[\r\n                <Button \r\n                  type=\"primary\" \r\n                  onClick={() => viewChildDetails(child.uuid)}\r\n                >\r\n                  View Details\r\n                </Button>\r\n              ]}\r\n            >\r\n              <List.Item.Meta\r\n                avatar={<Avatar icon={<UserOutlined />} />}\r\n                title={child.name}\r\n                description={`Class: ${child.class_name} | Email: ${child.email}`}\r\n              />\r\n            </List.Item>\r\n          )}\r\n        />\r\n      </Card>\r\n    </div>\r\n  );\r\n}\r\n</code></pre>\r\n\r\n<h3>Child Details Page</h3>\r\n\r\n<pre><code>// app/parent/children/[uuid]/page.tsx\r\n'use client';\r\n\r\nimport { useState, useEffect } from 'react';\r\nimport { Card, Tabs, Table, Statistic, Row, Col } from 'antd';\r\nimport { useParams } from 'next/navigation';\r\nimport axios from 'axios';\r\nimport { getAuthHeaders } from '@/app/lib/auth';\r\n\r\nexport default function ChildDetailsPage() {\r\n  const params = useParams();\r\n  const childUuid = params.uuid as string;\r\n  const [childDetails, setChildDetails] = useState<any>(null);\r\n  const [attendance, setAttendance] = useState([]);\r\n  const [results, setResults] = useState([]);\r\n  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true);\r\n\r\n  useEffect(() => {\r\n    if (childUuid) {\r\n      fetchChildDetails();\r\n      fetchAttendance();\r\n      fetchResults();\r\n    }\r\n  }, [childUuid]);\r\n\r\n  const fetchChildDetails = async () => {\r\n    try {\r\n      const response = await axios.get(\r\n        `http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/parent/children/${childUuid}/details`,\r\n        getAuthHeaders()\r\n      );\r\n\r\n      if (response.data.status === 'success') {\r\n        setChildDetails(response.data.data);\r\n      }\r\n    } catch (error) {\r\n      console.error('Error fetching child details:', error);\r\n    } finally {\r\n      setLoading(false);\r\n    }\r\n  };\r\n\r\n  const fetchAttendance = async () => {\r\n    try {\r\n      const response = await axios.get(\r\n        `http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/parent/children/${childUuid}/attendance`,\r\n        getAuthHeaders()\r\n      );\r\n\r\n      if (response.data.status === 'success') {\r\n        setAttendance(response.data.data);\r\n      }\r\n    } catch (error) {\r\n      console.error('Error fetching attendance:', error);\r\n    }\r\n  };\r\n\r\n  const fetchResults = async () => {\r\n    try {\r\n      const response = await axios.get(\r\n        `http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/parent/children/${childUuid}/results`,\r\n        getAuthHeaders()\r\n      );\r\n\r\n      if (response.data.status === 'success') {\r\n        setResults(response.data.data);\r\n      }\r\n    } catch (error) {\r\n      console.error('Error fetching results:', error);\r\n    }\r\n  };\r\n\r\n  const tabItems = [\r\n    {\r\n      key: 'overview',\r\n      label: 'Overview',\r\n      children: (\r\n        <div>\r\n          <Row gutter={16}>\r\n            <Col span={8}>\r\n              <Statistic title=\"Class\" value={childDetails?.class_name} />\r\n            </Col>\r\n            <Col span={8}>\r\n              <Statistic title=\"Email\" value={childDetails?.email} />\r\n            </Col>\r\n            <Col span={8}>\r\n              <Statistic title=\"Phone\" value={childDetails?.phone} />\r\n            </Col>\r\n          </Row>\r\n        </div>\r\n      )\r\n    },\r\n    {\r\n      key: 'attendance',\r\n      label: 'Attendance',\r\n      children: (\r\n        <Table\r\n          dataSource={attendance}\r\n          columns={[\r\n            { title: 'Date', dataIndex: 'date', key: 'date' },\r\n            { title: 'Status', dataIndex: 'status', key: 'status' }\r\n          ]}\r\n        />\r\n      )\r\n    },\r\n    {\r\n      key: 'results',\r\n      label: 'Results',\r\n      children: (\r\n        <Table\r\n          dataSource={results}\r\n          columns={[\r\n            { title: 'Subject', dataIndex: 'subject', key: 'subject' },\r\n            { title: 'Score', dataIndex: 'score', key: 'score' },\r\n            { title: 'Grade', dataIndex: 'grade', key: 'grade' }\r\n          ]}\r\n        />\r\n      )\r\n    }\r\n  ];\r\n\r\n  return (\r\n    <div className=\"child-details-page\">\r\n      <Card title={childDetails?.name || 'Child Details'}>\r\n        <Tabs items={tabItems} />\r\n      </Card>\r\n    </div>\r\n  );\r\n}\r\n</code></pre>\r\n\r\n<h2>Key Features Summary</h2>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n    <thead>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <th>Feature</th>\r\n            <th>Description</th>\r\n            <th>Access Level</th>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </thead>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>Children List</td>\r\n            <td>View all registered children</td>\r\n            <td>Read-only</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>Child Details</td>\r\n            <td>View comprehensive child information</td>\r\n            <td>Read-only</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>Attendance Monitoring</td>\r\n            <td>View children's attendance records and statistics</td>\r\n            <td>Read-only</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>Academic Results</td>\r\n            <td>View children's academic performance and results</td>\r\n            <td>Read-only</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>Fee Information</td>\r\n            <td>View fee obligations and payment history</td>\r\n            <td>Read-only</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>Profile Management</td>\r\n            <td>View and update personal profile information</td>\r\n            <td>Read/Write</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"important-box\">\r\n    <h4>Important Notes</h4>\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li>Parents can only view information for their registered children</li>\r\n        <li>All parent access is read-only except for profile management</li>\r\n        <li>Children must be linked to parents during student registration</li>\r\n        <li>Parents receive notifications about important academic events</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"success-box\">\r\n    <h4>Next Steps</h4>\r\n    <p>Review the Database Design section to understand the data relationships, or explore Future Enhancements for planned features.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n";
sectionContent['database'] = "<h1>Database Design Overview</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>This section provides an overview of the database structure, key relationships, and data models used in the School Management System.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Core Entities</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The database is organized around several core entities that represent the main components of the school management system.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>1. Users Table</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The users table stores information for all system users (students, teachers, parents, and admins).</p>\r\n\r\n<pre><code>users: id, uuid, name, email, phone, password, role, parent_id, created_at, updated_at</code></pre>\r\n\r\n<h3>2. Timetable Table</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Stores class timetable information.</p>\r\n\r\n<pre><code>timetable: id, class_id, subject_id, day_of_week, start_time, end_time, teacher_id, created_at, updated_at</code></pre>\r\n\r\n<h3>3. Academic Sessions Table</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Stores academic session information (e.g., 2024/2025, 2025/2026).</p>\r\n\r\n<pre><code>academic_sessions: id, name, start_date, end_date, current, created_at, updated_at</code></pre>\r\n\r\n<h3>4. Announcements Table</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Stores system announcements and notifications.</p>\r\n\r\n<pre><code>announcements: id, title, description, target_role['admin', 'teacher', 'student', 'parent', 'all'], start_date, end_date, created_at, updated_at</code></pre>\r\n\r\n<h3>5. Terms Table</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Stores academic term information within sessions.</p>\r\n\r\n<pre><code>terms: id, academic_session_id, name, start_date, end_date, created_at, updated_at</code></pre>\r\n\r\n<h3>6. Class Subject Table</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Pivot table linking classes to subjects (many-to-many relationship).</p>\r\n\r\n<pre><code>class_subject: id, class_id, subject_id, teacher_id, created_at, updated_at</code></pre>\r\n\r\n<h3>7. Student Classes Table</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Links students to classes and sessions.</p>\r\n\r\n<pre><code>student_classes: id, student_id, class_id, session_id, created_at, updated_at</code></pre>\r\n\r\n<h3>8. Attendance Table</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Stores daily attendance records.</p>\r\n\r\n<pre><code>attendance: id, student_id, class_id, term_id, session_id, date, status['present', 'absent', 'late'], teacher_id, created_at, updated_at</code></pre>\r\n\r\n<h3>9. Results Table</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Stores academic results and scores.</p>\r\n\r\n<pre><code>results: id, student_id, subject_id, term_id, teacher_id, ca1, ca2, exam_score, total, grade, teacher_comment, created_at, updated_at</code></pre>\r\n\r\n<h3>10. Fees Table</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Stores fee structures and obligations.</p>\r\n\r\n<pre><code>fees: id, class_id, session_id, fee_type, amount_due, term, created_at, updated_at</code></pre>\r\n\r\n<h3>11. Books Table</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Stores bookshop inventory.</p>\r\n\r\n<pre><code>books: id, branch_id, uuid, book_name, class_level_id, term_id, quantity, initial_quantity, cost_price, selling_price, created_at, updated_at</code></pre>\r\n\r\n<h3>12. Notifications Table</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Stores system notifications.</p>\r\n\r\n<pre><code>notifications: id, title, message, target_role, user_id (nullable), sent_at, read_at, created_at, updated_at</code></pre>\r\n\r\n<h3>13. Password Resets Table</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Stores password reset tokens.</p>\r\n\r\n<pre><code>password_resets: id, email, token, expires_at, created_at, updated_at</code></pre>\r\n\r\n<h3>14. Events Table</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Stores school events and activities.</p>\r\n\r\n<pre><code>events: id, title, description, start_date, end_date, target_role['student', 'teacher', 'parent', 'all'], created_at, updated_at</code></pre>\r\n\r\n<h3>15. Materials Table</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Stores learning materials and resources.</p>\r\n\r\n<pre><code>materials: id, class_id, subject_id, teacher_id, file_path, description, created_at, updated_at</code></pre>\r\n\r\n<h3>16. Book Sales Table</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Stores book sales transactions.</p>\r\n\r\n<pre><code>book_sales: id, student_id, book_id, branch_id, quantity, total_price, purchased_at, created_at, updated_at</code></pre>\r\n\r\n<h3>17. Classes Table</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Stores class information and academic levels.</p>\r\n\r\n<pre><code>classes: id, name, arm, class_level_id, class_teacher_id, created_at, updated_at</code></pre>\r\n\r\n<h3>18. Subjects Table</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Stores subject information.</p>\r\n\r\n<pre><code>subjects: id, name, code, created_at, updated_at</code></pre>\r\n\r\n<h3>19. Payments Table</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Stores payment transactions.</p>\r\n\r\n<pre><code>payments: id, parent_id, student_id, total_amount, method, reference, status, payment_date, created_at, updated_at</code></pre>\r\n\r\n<h3>20. Payment Allocations Table</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Stores payment allocation details.</p>\r\n\r\n<pre><code>payment_allocations: id, payment_id, fee_id, amount, created_at, updated_at</code></pre>\r\n\r\n<h3>21. Student Fees Table</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Stores student fee obligations and payments.</p>\r\n\r\n<pre><code>student_fees: id, student_id, fee_id, amount_due, amount_paid, status, created_at, updated_at</code></pre>\r\n\r\n<h3>22. Subject Teachers Table</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Links teachers to subjects and classes.</p>\r\n\r\n<pre><code>subject_teachers: id, teacher_id, class_id, subject_id, session_id, created_at, updated_at</code></pre>\r\n\r\n<h3>23. Class Levels Table</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Stores class level information.</p>\r\n\r\n<pre><code>class_levels: id, name, created_at, updated_at</code></pre>\r\n\r\n<h3>24. Branches Table</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Stores school branch information.</p>\r\n\r\n<pre><code>branches: id, uuid, name, location, created_at, updated_at</code></pre>\r\n\r\n<h3>25. Book Returns Table</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Stores book return transactions.</p>\r\n\r\n<pre><code>book_returns: id, book_id, student_id, branch_id, quantity, refund_amount, reason, returned_at, created_at, updated_at</code></pre>\r\n\r\n<h3>26. School Profiles Table</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Stores school profile and information.</p>\r\n\r\n<pre><code>school_profiles: id, school_name, motto, mission, vision, about_us, logo_path, address, email, phone, website, established_year, created_at, updated_at</code></pre>\r\n\r\n<h3>27. Leadership Team Table</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Stores leadership team information.</p>\r\n\r\n<pre><code>leadership_team: id, school_id, name, position, photo_path, bio, display_order, created_at, updated_at</code></pre>\r\n\r\n<h3>28. Tuition Fees Table</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Stores tuition fee structures.</p>\r\n\r\n<pre><code>tuition_fees: id, school_id, class_category, amount, billing_cycle, fee_cover, effective_from, effective_to, created_at, updated_at</code></pre>\r\n\r\n<h3>29. Blogs Table</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Stores blog posts and articles.</p>\r\n\r\n<pre><code>blogs: id, school_id, title, slug, excerpt, content, featured_image, author_name, status, published_at, created_at, updated_at</code></pre>\r\n\r\n<h2>Key Relationships</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>User Relationships</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><strong>Users â†’ Student Classes:</strong> One-to-Many (A user can be enrolled in multiple classes over time)</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Users â†’ Parent-Child:</strong> One-to-Many (A parent can have multiple children)</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Users â†’ Attendances:</strong> One-to-Many (A student has many attendance records)</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Users â†’ Results:</strong> One-to-Many (A student has many results)</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Users â†’ Fees:</strong> One-to-Many (A student has multiple fee obligations)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Class Relationships</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><strong>Classes â†’ Subjects:</strong> Many-to-Many (via class_subjects table)</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Classes â†’ Students:</strong> Many-to-Many (via student_classes table)</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Classes â†’ Teachers:</strong> Many-to-Many (via teacher_assignments table)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Academic Relationships</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><strong>Sessions â†’ All Academic Data:</strong> One-to-Many (All academic records are tied to a session)</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Subjects â†’ Results:</strong> One-to-Many (A subject has many results)</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Subjects â†’ Attendances:</strong> One-to-Many (Attendance is tracked per subject)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Database Design Principles</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"info-box\">\r\n    <h4>Design Principles</h4>\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li><strong>Normalization:</strong> Database follows 3NF to reduce redundancy</li>\r\n        <li><strong>Foreign Keys:</strong> All relationships are enforced with foreign key constraints</li>\r\n        <li><strong>UUID Usage:</strong> Users are identified by UUIDs for security and scalability</li>\r\n        <li><strong>Soft Deletes:</strong> Critical data uses soft deletes (deleted_at) for audit trails</li>\r\n        <li><strong>Timestamps:</strong> All tables include created_at and updated_at for tracking</li>\r\n        <li><strong>Indexing:</strong> Key fields (email, uuid, foreign keys) are indexed for performance</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h2>Data Flow Examples</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>Student Registration Flow</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n    <li>Parent registers â†’ Creates user record with role='parent'</li>\r\n    <li>Student registers â†’ Creates user record with role='student' and parent_id</li>\r\n    <li>Admin assigns class â†’ Creates student_classes record</li>\r\n    <li>System creates fee obligations â†’ Creates fees records</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3>Attendance Marking Flow</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n    <li>Teacher selects class and date</li>\r\n    <li>System fetches students from student_classes</li>\r\n    <li>Teacher marks attendance for each student</li>\r\n    <li>System creates attendance records</li>\r\n    <li>Students and parents can view attendance</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3>Results Entry Flow</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n    <li>Teacher selects class, subject, and exam type</li>\r\n    <li>System fetches students from student_classes</li>\r\n    <li>Teacher enters scores for each student</li>\r\n    <li>System creates results records</li>\r\n    <li>System calculates grades based on scores</li>\r\n    <li>Students and parents can view results</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h2>Indexes and Performance</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Key indexes are created on:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><code>users.email</code> - For fast login lookups</li>\r\n    <li><code>users.uuid</code> - For user identification</li>\r\n    <li><code>users.role</code> - For role-based queries</li>\r\n    <li><code>student_classes.student_uuid</code> - For student class lookups</li>\r\n    <li><code>student_classes.class_id</code> - For class student lists</li>\r\n    <li><code>attendances.student_uuid</code> - For attendance history</li>\r\n    <li><code>attendances.date</code> - For date-based queries</li>\r\n    <li><code>results.student_uuid</code> - For result lookups</li>\r\n    <li><code>fees.student_uuid</code> - For fee queries</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Data Integrity</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"important-box\">\r\n    <h4>Data Integrity Measures</h4>\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li><strong>Cascade Deletes:</strong> Configured where appropriate (e.g., deleting a class removes class_subjects)</li>\r\n        <li><strong>Restrict Deletes:</strong> Used for critical data (e.g., cannot delete user with attendance records)</li>\r\n        <li><strong>Unique Constraints:</strong> Email, class codes, subject codes are unique</li>\r\n        <li><strong>Check Constraints:</strong> Status fields have valid value checks</li>\r\n        <li><strong>Default Values:</strong> Sensible defaults for optional fields</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h2>Backup and Recovery</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Recommended backup strategy:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><strong>Daily Backups:</strong> Full database backup every night</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Transaction Logs:</strong> Maintain transaction logs for point-in-time recovery</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Offsite Storage:</strong> Store backups in multiple locations</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Test Restores:</strong> Regularly test backup restoration procedures</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Migration and Seeding</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The database uses migrations for schema management:</p>\r\n\r\n<pre><code>// Example migration structure\r\nphp artisan make:migration create_users_table\r\nphp artisan make:migration create_classes_table\r\nphp artisan make:migration create_attendances_table\r\n// ... etc\r\n\r\n// Seed initial data\r\nphp artisan db:seed --class=RolesSeeder\r\nphp artisan db:seed --class=AdminUserSeeder\r\n</code></pre>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"success-box\">\r\n    <h4>Database Best Practices</h4>\r\n    <p>Always use migrations for schema changes, maintain foreign key relationships, and regularly optimize queries for performance. Monitor database performance and adjust indexes as needed.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n";
sectionContent['enhancements'] = "<h1>Future Enhancements</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>This section outlines planned features, improvements, and enhancements for the School Management System. These enhancements aim to improve user experience, add new functionality, and keep the system modern and competitive.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"screenshot-container\">\r\n    <img src=\"assets/screenshots/login-page.png\" alt=\"User Login Interface\" class=\"screenshot-image\" loading=\"lazy\">\r\n    <div class=\"screenshot-caption\">Figure 1: User Login Interface</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h2>Short-Term Enhancements (Next 3-6 Months)</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>1. Enhanced Reporting & Analytics</h3>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"feature-grid\">\r\n    <div class=\"feature-card\">\r\n        <h4>ðŸ“Š Advanced Dashboards</h4>\r\n        <p>Interactive dashboards with customizable widgets, real-time data visualization, and export capabilities</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class=\"feature-card\">\r\n        <h4>ðŸ“ˆ Performance Analytics</h4>\r\n        <p>Student performance trends, class comparisons, and predictive analytics for academic outcomes</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class=\"feature-card\">\r\n        <h4>ðŸ“‹ Custom Reports</h4>\r\n        <p>Report builder for creating custom reports with filters, grouping, and multiple export formats</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h3>2. Mobile Application</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><strong>Native Mobile Apps:</strong> iOS and Android applications for students, teachers, and parents</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Push Notifications:</strong> Real-time notifications for attendance, results, fees, and announcements</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Offline Mode:</strong> Basic functionality available offline with sync when online</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Mobile-Optimized UI:</strong> Touch-friendly interface optimized for mobile devices</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>3. Communication Features</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><strong>In-App Messaging:</strong> Direct messaging between teachers, students, and parents</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Announcement System:</strong> Enhanced announcement system with categories and targeting</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Email Integration:</strong> Automated email notifications for important events</li>\r\n    <li><strong>SMS Notifications:</strong> SMS alerts for critical updates (attendance, fees, results)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>4. Enhanced Attendance System</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><strong>QR Code Attendance:</strong> QR code-based attendance marking for faster processing</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Biometric Integration:</strong> Fingerprint or facial recognition for attendance</li>\r\n    <li><strong>GPS Verification:</strong> Location-based attendance verification</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Bulk Attendance:</strong> Mark attendance for entire class with one action</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Medium-Term Enhancements (6-12 Months)</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>5. Learning Management System (LMS) Integration</h3>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"feature-grid\">\r\n    <div class=\"feature-card\">\r\n        <h4>ðŸ“š Course Management</h4>\r\n        <p>Create and manage online courses, assignments, and learning materials</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class=\"feature-card\">\r\n        <h4>ðŸ“ Assignment Submission</h4>\r\n        <p>Digital assignment submission and grading system</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class=\"feature-card\">\r\n        <h4>ðŸ’¬ Discussion Forums</h4>\r\n        <p>Class discussion forums for student-teacher interaction</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class=\"feature-card\">\r\n        <h4>ðŸ“¹ Video Integration</h4>\r\n        <p>Video lessons and live class streaming capabilities</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h3>6. Financial Management Enhancements</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><strong>Payment Gateway Integration:</strong> Online payment processing with multiple gateways</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Fee Reminders:</strong> Automated fee reminders via email and SMS</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Payment Plans:</strong> Flexible payment plan options for parents</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Financial Reports:</strong> Comprehensive financial reporting and analytics</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Receipt Generation:</strong> Automated receipt generation and email delivery</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>7. Library Management System</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><strong>Book Catalog:</strong> Comprehensive library catalog with search and filtering</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Book Issuance:</strong> Digital book issuance and return tracking</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Due Date Reminders:</strong> Automated reminders for book returns</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Fine Management:</strong> Automatic fine calculation and collection</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>8. Examination Management</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><strong>Exam Scheduling:</strong> Automated exam timetable generation</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Seat Allocation:</strong> Automatic seat allocation for exams</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Hall Ticket Generation:</strong> Automated hall ticket generation</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Result Processing:</strong> Enhanced result processing and grade calculation</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Long-Term Enhancements (12+ Months)</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>9. Artificial Intelligence & Machine Learning</h3>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"info-box\">\r\n    <h4>AI-Powered Features</h4>\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li><strong>Predictive Analytics:</strong> Predict student performance and identify at-risk students</li>\r\n        <li><strong>Personalized Learning:</strong> AI-driven personalized learning paths</li>\r\n        <li><strong>Automated Grading:</strong> AI-powered automated grading for objective questions</li>\r\n        <li><strong>Chatbot Support:</strong> AI chatbot for answering common queries</li>\r\n        <li><strong>Smart Recommendations:</strong> Recommend courses, books, and resources</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h3>10. Advanced Security Features</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><strong>Two-Factor Authentication (2FA):</strong> Enhanced security with 2FA</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Single Sign-On (SSO):</strong> SSO integration with other systems</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Audit Logging:</strong> Comprehensive audit logs for all system actions</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Data Encryption:</strong> End-to-end encryption for sensitive data</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Role-Based Permissions:</strong> Granular permission system</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>11. Integration Capabilities</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><strong>Third-Party Integrations:</strong> Integration with popular educational tools</li>\r\n    <li><strong>API Marketplace:</strong> Public API for third-party developers</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Webhook Support:</strong> Webhook notifications for external systems</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Data Export/Import:</strong> Enhanced data import/export capabilities</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>12. Multi-Language Support</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><strong>Internationalization (i18n):</strong> Support for multiple languages</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Localization:</strong> Region-specific date, time, and currency formats</li>\r\n    <li><strong>RTL Support:</strong> Right-to-left language support</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Technical Improvements</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>Performance Enhancements</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><strong>Caching Strategy:</strong> Implement Redis caching for frequently accessed data</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Database Optimization:</strong> Query optimization and database indexing</li>\r\n    <li><strong>CDN Integration:</strong> Content delivery network for static assets</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Lazy Loading:</strong> Implement lazy loading for images and components</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Code Splitting:</strong> Optimize bundle sizes with code splitting</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>User Experience Improvements</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><strong>Dark Mode:</strong> System-wide dark mode support</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Accessibility:</strong> WCAG 2.1 AA compliance for accessibility</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Keyboard Shortcuts:</strong> Power user keyboard shortcuts</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Customizable UI:</strong> User-customizable interface themes</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Progressive Web App (PWA):</strong> PWA capabilities for app-like experience</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Development & DevOps</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><strong>Automated Testing:</strong> Comprehensive unit, integration, and E2E tests</li>\r\n    <li><strong>CI/CD Pipeline:</strong> Continuous integration and deployment</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Monitoring & Logging:</strong> Advanced monitoring and logging solutions</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Documentation:</strong> Enhanced API and code documentation</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Microservices Architecture:</strong> Consider microservices for scalability</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Feature Request Process</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"success-box\">\r\n    <h4>How to Request Features</h4>\r\n    <p>Users and stakeholders can submit feature requests through:</p>\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li>In-app feedback form</li>\r\n        <li>Email to development team</li>\r\n        <li>GitHub issues (for open-source contributions)</li>\r\n        <li>User surveys and feedback sessions</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    <p>All requests are evaluated based on:</p>\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li>User demand and priority</li>\r\n        <li>Technical feasibility</li>\r\n        <li>Resource requirements</li>\r\n        <li>Alignment with system goals</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h2>Roadmap Timeline</h2>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n    <thead>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <th>Quarter</th>\r\n            <th>Focus Area</th>\r\n            <th>Key Features</th>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </thead>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>Q1 2025</td>\r\n            <td>Reporting & Analytics</td>\r\n            <td>Advanced dashboards, custom reports, performance analytics</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>Q2 2025</td>\r\n            <td>Mobile & Communication</td>\r\n            <td>Mobile apps, messaging, enhanced notifications</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>Q3 2025</td>\r\n            <td>LMS Integration</td>\r\n            <td>Course management, assignments, video integration</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>Q4 2025</td>\r\n            <td>Financial & Library</td>\r\n            <td>Payment gateways, library management, exam system</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>2026+</td>\r\n            <td>AI & Advanced Features</td>\r\n            <td>AI-powered features, advanced security, integrations</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"important-box\">\r\n    <h4>Note</h4>\r\n    <p>This roadmap is subject to change based on user feedback, technical constraints, and business priorities. Features may be added, removed, or reprioritized as needed.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h2>Contributing to Enhancements</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>We welcome contributions from the community:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><strong>Code Contributions:</strong> Submit pull requests for bug fixes and features</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Documentation:</strong> Help improve documentation and guides</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Testing:</strong> Participate in beta testing of new features</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Feedback:</strong> Provide feedback and suggestions for improvements</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"success-box\">\r\n    <h4>Stay Updated</h4>\r\n    <p>Follow our development blog and release notes to stay informed about new features and enhancements. Your feedback helps shape the future of the School Management System!</p>\r\n</div>\r\n";

